DRC Mining Week 2018 was a significant success. Held at the Grand Karavia Hotel in Lubumbashi on 13 – 15 June, it all major copper/cobalt producers attend, present and exhibit – a clear demonstration of the value they place on the conference. And the focus was not just about production and achievements but also about long-term commitments to uplifting the DRC – through employment, upskilling, economic upliftment and sustainable business practices. This article first appeared in Mining Review Africa Issue 7 2018. It will be published online on the 7th June 2018. You can read the full digital magazine here or subscribe here to receive a print copy